"The Climb" is the first single from the soundtrack to the motion picture Hannah Montana: The Movie. The song will act as Cyrus' debut single as a solo artist to country radio. The song will officially be released to the country format on March 9, 2009. As of February 2009, the song has charted on the Billboard Pop 100 chart. The song debuted at #48 on the Hot Country Songs chart for the chart week of March 14, 2009.

The video was release on February 11, 2009 on Cyrus' MySpace page. The video shows Cyrus' walking down a road, holding a guitar, with scenes of the movie playing in the background throughout. When it begins to rain, Cyrus takes her jacket off and plays her guitar. Toward the conclusion of the video, she is seen on a cliff, and the camera pans around her as she sings.

As a solo artist, "The Climb" will be Cyrus' first solo release to country radio as well as pop radios, since charting the #4 hit, "Ready, Set, Don't Go" with her dad Billy Ray Cyrus in 2007. The song debuted at #48 on the Hot Country Songs chart on the chart week of March 14, 2009. Cyrus performed the song during the Kid's Inaugural on Disney Channel on January 19, 2009.
